    ('Barbarian: Reckless Attack', 'You can throw aside all concern for defense to attack with increased ferocity. When you make your first attack roll on your turn, you can decide to attack recklessly. Doing so gives you Advantage on attack rolls using Strength until the start of your next turn, but attack rolls against you have Advantage during that time.'),
    ('Barbarian: Relentless Rage', 'Your Rage can keep you fighting despite grievous wounds. If you drop to 0 Hit Points while your Rage is active and don’t die outright, you can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. If you succeed, your Hit Points instead change to a number equal to twice your Barbarian level. Each time you use this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. When you finish a Short or Long Rest, the DC resets to 10.'),
    ('Barbarian: Unarmored Defense', 'While you aren’t wearing any armor, your base Armor Class equals 10 plus your Dexterity and Constitution modifiers. You can use a Shield and still gain this benefit.'),
    ('Barbarian: Weapon Mastery', 'Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery properties of two kinds of Simple or Martial Melee weapons of your choice. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can practice weapon drills and change one of those weapon choices. When you reach certain Barbarian levels, you gain the ability to use the mastery properties of more kinds of weapons, as shown in the Weapon Mastery column of the Barbarian Features table.'),
    ('Bard (College of Dance): Dazzling Footwork', 'While unarmored and not using a Shield, gain dance-based Performance Advantage, AC = 10 + Dex + Cha, and enhanced Unarmed Strikes tied to your Bardic Inspiration die.'),
    ('Bard (College of Dance): Inspiring Movement', 'When a visible enemy ends its turn within 5 feet, expend Bardic Inspiration as a Reaction to move yourself and one nearby ally up to half Speed without Opportunity Attacks.'),
    ('Bard (College of Dance): Leading Evasion', 'Against effects allowing a Dexterity save for half damage, take none on a success and half on a failure; nearby creatures making the same save can share this benefit.'),
    ('Bard (College of Dance): Tandem Footwork', 'When rolling Initiative, expend Bardic Inspiration to add the die roll to your Initiative and nearby allies who can see or hear you.'),
    ('Bard (College of Glamour): Beguiling Magic', 'Always prepare Charm Person and Mirror Image. After casting an Enchantment or Illusion spell with a slot, try to Charm or Frighten a visible creature; refresh after a Long Rest or by spending Bardic Inspiration.'),
    ('Bard (College of Glamour): Mantle of Inspiration', 'Bonus Action to expend Bardic Inspiration, grant Temporary Hit Points to nearby creatures, and let each move as a Reaction without Opportunity Attacks.'),
    ('Bard (College of Glamour): Mantle of Majesty', 'Always prepare Command. As a Bonus Action, cast it without a slot and keep casting it as a Bonus Action for 1 minute while concentrating; refresh with a Long Rest or a level 3+ spell slot.'),
    ('Bard (College of Glamour): Unbreakable Majesty', 'Bonus Action to assume a majestic presence; the first attacker to hit you each turn must pass a Charisma save or miss.'),
    ('Bard (College of Lore): Bonus Proficiencies', 'You gain proficiency with three skills of your choice.'),
    ('Bard (College of Lore): Cutting Words', 'Reaction to expend Bardic Inspiration and subtract the die from a visible creature''s damage roll, successful ability check, or successful attack roll.'),
    ('Bard (College of Lore): Magical Discoveries', 'Choose two always-prepared spells from the Cleric, Druid, or Wizard spell lists; they must be cantrips or spells you can cast with your slots.'),
    ('Bard (College of Lore): Peerless Skill', 'When you fail an ability check or attack roll, expend Bardic Inspiration to add the die and potentially succeed; keep the use if you still fail.'),
    ('Bard (College of Valor): Battle Magic', 'When you use an Action to cast a spell, you can make one weapon attack as a Bonus Action.'),
    ('Bard (College of Valor): Combat Inspiration', 'Allies can use your Bardic Inspiration to add to damage or AC against an attack.'),
    ('Bard (College of Valor): Extra Attack', 'You can attack twice. You can replace one of these attacks with a Cantrip.'),
    ('Bard (College of Valor): Martial Training', 'Gain proficiency with Medium Armor, Shields, and Martial Weapons. Use a weapon as a spell focus.'),
    ('Bard: Bardic Inspiration', 'Bonus Action to grant one creature within 60 feet a Bardic Inspiration die it can add after failing a D20 Test, potentially turning the failure into a success.'),
    ('Bard: Countercharm', 'Reaction when you or a creature within 30 feet fails a save against Charmed or Frightened; force a reroll with Advantage.'),
    ('Bard: Epic Boon', 'You gain an Epic Boon feat or another feat for which you qualify.'),
    ('Bard: Expertise', 'Choose two more skill proficiencies for Expertise.'),
    ('Bard: Font of Inspiration', 'Regain Bardic Inspiration uses on a Short or Long Rest, and spend a spell slot to regain one use.'),
    ('Bard: Jack of All Trades', 'Add half your Proficiency Bonus to ability checks using skills you lack proficiency in.'),
    ('Bard: Magical Secrets', 'When your prepared spell count increases or you replace a Bard spell, you can choose from the Bard, Cleric, Druid, and Wizard spell lists.'),
    ('Bard: Spellcasting', 'Cast prepared Bard spells using Charisma. You start with two Bard cantrips and four level 1 prepared spells, and use a Musical Instrument as a spellcasting focus.'),
    ('Bard: Superior Inspiration', 'When you roll Initiative, regain Bardic Inspiration uses until you have two if you have fewer than two.'),
    ('Bard: Words of Creation', 'Always prepare Power Word Heal and Power Word Kill. When you cast either spell, you can also target a second creature within 10 feet of the first.'),
    ('Cleric (Life Domain): Blessed Healer', 'After you cast a spell with a spell slot that restores HP to another creature, you regain HP equal to 2 plus the spell slot level.'),
    ('Cleric (Life Domain): Disciple of Life', 'When a spell you cast with a spell slot restores HP, the target regains extra HP equal to 2 plus the spell slot level.'),
    ('Cleric (Life Domain): Life Domain Spells', 'Always prepare Aid, Bless, Cure Wounds, and Lesser Restoration; later add Mass Healing Word, Revivify, Aura of Life, Death Ward, Greater Restoration, and Mass Cure Wounds.'),
    ('Cleric (Life Domain): Preserve Life', 'Magic Action using Channel Divinity to restore HP equal to 5 times your Cleric level, divided among Bloodied creatures within 30 feet and not above half HP.'),
    ('Cleric (Life Domain): Supreme Healing', 'When you would roll dice to restore HP with a spell or Channel Divinity, use the highest possible result for each die instead.'),
    ('Cleric (Light Domain): Corona of Light', 'Magic Action to emit sunlight for 1 minute. Enemies in the bright light have Disadvantage on saves against Radiance of the Dawn and Fire or Radiant spells.'),
    ('Cleric (Light Domain): Improved Warding Flare', 'Regain Warding Flare uses on Short or Long Rest, and grant Temporary Hit Points to the target of the triggering attack when you use it.'),
    ('Cleric (Light Domain): Light Domain Spells', 'Always prepare Burning Hands, Faerie Fire, Scorching Ray, and See Invisibility; later add Daylight, Fireball, Arcane Eye, Wall of Fire, Flame Strike, and Scrying.'),
    ('Cleric (Light Domain): Radiance of the Dawn', 'Magic Action using Channel Divinity to dispel magical Darkness and deal Radiant damage in a 30-foot Emanation.'),
    ('Cleric (Light Domain): Warding Flare', 'Reaction when a visible creature within 30 feet makes an attack roll, imposing Disadvantage on that roll. Uses equal Wisdom modifier per Long Rest.'),
    ('Cleric (Trickery Domain): Blessing of the Trickster', 'Magic Action to give yourself or a willing creature within 30 feet Advantage on Stealth checks until your next Long Rest or until you use this feature again.'),
    ('Cleric (Trickery Domain): Improved Duplicity', 'Your Invoke Duplicity illusion grants allies Advantage against nearby enemies and heals a nearby creature when the illusion ends.'),
    ('Cleric (Trickery Domain): Invoke Duplicity', 'Bonus Action using Channel Divinity to create an illusory duplicate for 1 minute. Cast from its space, distract nearby enemies, and move it as a Bonus Action.'),
    ('Cleric (Trickery Domain): Trickery Domain Spells', 'Always prepare Charm Person, Disguise Self, Invisibility, and Pass without Trace; later add Hypnotic Pattern, Nondetection, Confusion, Dimension Door, Dominate Person, and Modify Memory.'),
    ('Cleric (Trickery Domain): Trickster''s Transposition', 'Whenever you create or move your Invoke Duplicity illusion as a Bonus Action, you can teleport by swapping places with it.'),
    ('Cleric (War Domain): Avatar of Battle', 'Gain Resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage.'),
    ('Cleric (War Domain): Guided Strike', 'When you or a creature within 30 feet misses with an attack roll, expend Channel Divinity to add +10, using your Reaction if the roll is not yours.'),
    ('Cleric (War Domain): War Domain Spells', 'Always prepare Guiding Bolt, Magic Weapon, Shield of Faith, and Spiritual Weapon; later add Crusader''s Mantle, Spirit Guardians, Fire Shield, Freedom of Movement, Hold Monster, and Steel Wind Strike.'),
    ('Cleric (War Domain): War God''s Blessing', 'Expend Channel Divinity to cast Shield of Faith or Spiritual Weapon without a spell slot or Concentration; the spell lasts 1 minute.'),
    ('Cleric (War Domain): War Priest', 'Bonus Action to make one weapon attack or Unarmed Strike. Uses equal Wisdom modifier per Short or Long Rest.'),
    ('Cleric: Blessed Strikes', 'Choose Divine Strike for extra Necrotic or Radiant weapon damage, or Potent Spellcasting to add Wisdom to Cleric cantrip damage.'),
    ('Cleric: Channel Divinity', 'Channel divine energy to fuel effects such as Divine Spark, Turn Undead, and subclass options. Regain uses on rests as shown by your Cleric level.'),
    ('Cleric: Divine Intervention', 'Magic Action to cast a Cleric spell of level 5 or lower without a spell slot or Material components, provided it does not require a Reaction.'),
    ('Cleric: Divine Order', 'Choose Protector for Martial weapons and Heavy armor, or Thaumaturge for one extra Cleric cantrip and a Wisdom-based bonus to Arcana or Religion checks.'),
    ('Cleric: Divine Spark', 'Magic Action to target a visible creature within 30 feet, either healing it or forcing a Constitution save against Necrotic or Radiant damage.'),
    ('Cleric: Epic Boon', 'You gain an Epic Boon feat or another feat for which you qualify.'),
    ('Cleric: Greater Divine Intervention', 'When you use Divine Intervention, you can choose Wish. If you do, you cannot use Divine Intervention again until you finish 2d4 Long Rests.'),
    ('Cleric: Improved Blessed Strikes', 'Your Blessed Strikes choice improves: Divine Strike deals 2d8 extra damage, or Potent Spellcasting grants Temporary Hit Points after damaging with a Cleric cantrip.'),
    ('Cleric: Sear Undead', 'When you use Turn Undead, roll d8s equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum one). Undead that fail the save take Radiant damage equal to the total without ending Turn Undead.'),
    ('Cleric: Spellcasting', 'Cast prepared Cleric spells using Wisdom. You start with three Cleric cantrips and four level 1 prepared spells, and use a Holy Symbol as a spellcasting focus.'),
