    ('Druid (Circle of the Land): Circle of the Land Spells', 'After each Long Rest, choose Arid, Polar, Temperate, or Tropical land; you always prepare that land''s spells for your Druid level and lower.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Land): Land''s Aid', 'Magic Action to expend Wild Shape, creating a 10-foot-radius burst within 60 feet. Chosen creatures take Necrotic damage, and one creature in the area regains HP.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Land): Natural Recovery', 'Cast one prepared Circle spell without a slot once per Long Rest, and recover spell slots after a Short Rest with combined level up to half your Druid level.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Land): Nature''s Sanctuary', 'Magic Action to expend Wild Shape and create a protective cube of spectral trees and vines. You and allies gain Half Cover, and allies share your Nature''s Ward Resistance.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Land): Nature''s Ward', 'You are immune to the Poisoned condition and gain Resistance tied to your current land choice: Fire, Cold, Lightning, or Poison.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Moon): Circle Forms', 'Your Wild Shape forms can have CR up to one-third your Druid level, your Beast AC can become 13 + Wisdom modifier, and you gain triple Druid level Temporary Hit Points.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Moon): Circle of the Moon Spells', 'Always prepare Cure Wounds, Moonbeam, and Starry Wisp; later add Conjure Animals, Fount of Moonlight, and Mass Cure Wounds. You can cast these spells in Wild Shape.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Moon): Improved Circle Forms', 'In Wild Shape, your attacks can deal Radiant damage instead of their normal type, and you add Wisdom to Constitution saves.'),
