    ('Druid (Circle of the Stars): Cosmic Omen', 'After each Long Rest, consult your Star Map. Until your next Long Rest, use a Reaction to add or subtract 1d6 from a visible creature''s D20 Test depending on the omen.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Stars): Full of Stars', 'While in Starry Form, you have resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Stars): Star Map', 'Create a star chart that can be a Druidic Focus. While holding it, you always prepare Guidance and Guiding Bolt and can cast Guiding Bolt without a spell slot.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Stars): Starry Form', 'Bonus Action to expend Wild Shape and take a luminous form for 10 minutes, choosing Archer for radiant attacks, Chalice for extra healing, or Dragon for reliable Wisdom, Intelligence, and Concentration checks.'),
    ('Druid (Circle of the Stars): Starry Form: Archer', 'While your Archer constellation is active, make a radiant ranged spell attack as a Bonus Action.'),
